messages.message:
Anyone seen a problem like then when trying to commit?

```
(venv-instabase) Edwards-MacBook-Pro-2:instabase eob$ git commit -am "OCR gRPC Server Stubs"
yapf.....................................................................Failed
hookid: yapf

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/Users/eob/.cache/pre-commit/repohAEIlf/py_env-python2.7/bin/yapf", line 11, in <module>
    sys.exit(run_main())
  File "/Users/eob/.cache/pre-commit/repohAEIlf/py_env-python2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/yapf/__init__.py", line 325, in run_main
    sys.exit(main(sys.argv))
  File "/Users/eob/.cache/pre-commit/repohAEIlf/py_env-python2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/yapf/__init__.py", line 213, in main
    verbose=args.verbose)
  File "/Users/eob/.cache/pre-commit/repohAEIlf/py_env-python2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/yapf/__init__.py", line 259, in FormatFiles
    changed |= future.result()
  File "/Users/eob/.cache/pre-commit/repohAEIlf/py_env-python2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/concurrent/futures/_base.py", line 455, in result
    return self.__get_result()
  File "/Users/eob/.cache/pre-commit/repohAEIlf/py_env-python2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/concurrent/futures/_base.py", line 414, in __get_result
    raise exception_type, self._exception, self._traceback
  File "<unknown>", line 12
    def mock_
            ^
SyntaxError: invalid syntax
```
Seems like yapf is blocking it because of `def mock_`, but doesn’t know what file (and the git diff doesn’t include that line…)
